  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "paragraph_name": "FUNC-CODES",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines a series of constants representing IMS (Information Management System) function codes. These codes are used when making calls to the IMS database to specify the type of operation to be performed. Each function code is a 4-character alphanumeric field, and they include codes for operations such as 'GU' (Get Unique), 'GHU' (Get Hold Unique), 'GN' (Get Next), 'GHN' (Get Hold Next), 'GNP' (Get Next within Parent), 'GHNP' (Get Hold Next within Parent), 'REPL' (Replace), 'ISRT' (Insert), and 'DLET' (Delete). These codes are used to build the Application Program Specification Block (PSB) when interacting with IMS.",
